.TH "WEBGLRENDERINGCONTEXT.TEXIMAGE2D" "3JS" "August 27, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebGLRenderingContext.texImage2D \- WebGLRenderingContext: texImage2D()
method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]texImage2D()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext\f[R] interface of the WebGL API specifies a
two\-dimensional texture image.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
// WebGL 1:
texImage2D(target, level, internalformat, width, height, border, format, type, srcData)
texImage2D(target, level, internalformat, format, type, source)

// Additionally available in WebGL 2:
texImage2D(target, level, internalformat, width, height, border, format, type, srcData, srcOffset)
texImage2D(target, level, internalformat, width, height, border, format, type, source)
texImage2D(target, level, internalformat, width, height, border, format, type, offset)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]target\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the binding point (target) of the active
texture.
Possible values:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_2D\f[R]: A two\-dimensional texture.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X\f[R]: Positive X face for a
cube\-mapped texture.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_X\f[R]: Negative X face for a
cube\-mapped texture.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Y\f[R]: Positive Y face for a
cube\-mapped texture.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Y\f[R]: Negative Y face for a
cube\-mapped texture.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Z\f[R]: Positive Z face for a
cube\-mapped texture.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Z\f[R]: Negative Z face for a
cube\-mapped texture.
.RE
.TP
\f[B]level\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLint\f[R] specifying the level of detail.
Level 0 is the base image level and level \f[I]n\f[R] is the n\-th
mipmap reduction level.
.TP
\f[B]internalformat\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying how the texture should be stored after
it\(cqs loaded.
See below for available values.
.TP
\f[B]width\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLsizei\f[R] specifying the width of the texture in texels.
.TP
\f[B]height\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLsizei\f[R] specifying the height of the texture in texels.
.TP
\f[B]border\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLint\f[R] specifying the width of the border.
Must be 0.
.TP
\f[B]format\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying how each integer element in the raw texel
data should be interpreted as color components.
In WebGL 1, this must be the same as \f[CR]internalformat\f[R].
See below for available values.
.TP
\f[B]type\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the size of each integer element in the
raw texel data.
.RS
.PP
The \f[CR]internalformat\f[R], \f[CR]format\f[R], and \f[CR]type\f[R]
values must be compatible with each other.
Possible combinations in both WebGL 1 and WebGL 2 (these internal
formats are \f[I]unsized\f[R] because you can\(cqt specify how many
bytes each pixel takes internally):
.PP
.TS
