.TE
.PP
When the \f[CR]OES_texture_float\f[R] extension is enabled,
\f[CR]type\f[R] can additionally be \f[CR]FLOAT\f[R].
When the \f[CR]OES_texture_half_float\f[R] extension is enabled,
\f[CR]type\f[R] can additionally be \f[CR]ext.HALF_FLOAT_OES\f[R]
(constant provided by the extension).
.PP
When the \f[CR]EXT_sRGB\f[R] extension is enabled,
\f[CR]internalformat\f[R] can additionally be \f[CR]ext.SRGB_EXT\f[R] or
\f[CR]ext.SRGB_ALPHA_EXT\f[R].
.PP
In WebGL 2, when specifying the source as \f[CR]srcData\f[R] or
\f[CR]offset\f[R], the following combinations are additionally available
(these internal formats are \f[I]sized\f[R] because the internal pixel
layout is exactly specified; we omit the input layout here because it
works similarly to the one above):
.PP
.TS
